Tottenham and Manchester United shared the spoils in a 1-1 draw at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium on Friday night. Steve Bergwijn gave Spurs the lead in the first half before Bruno Fernandes leveled the scored for United in the 81st minute after Paul Pogba was brought down inside the penalty area. VAR saved Jose Mourinho’s men in the stoppage time as the referee pointed for a penalty kick after Bruno Fernandes appeared to have been brought down by Eric Dier.